rComments: Super caring prof who goes above and beyond for his students! Has really great office hours and is always willing to meet in order to explain class material. As long as you pay attention in class, and read his rubric for the assignments, you should be able to do good. Would love to have professor Raahemi again!

it's a tough course, but if you take him he definitely makes it easier to understand the material. final was tough but it requires a good amount of studying so make sure you don't slack around otherwise you'll find the course hard (and blame the prof for it even though he teaches it well)

Highly recommend taking him! He explains concepts very well and he's always ready to re-explain if things aren't clear. I personally found the exam to be fine because I had practiced using the material he gave and emailed him whenever I was unsure of my answers (he responded even the night before the exam!) and he would always give detailed answers

I've had him twice so far and he's hands down the best prof for any BTM-related courses. So kind and he teaches really well and at a really good pace (may come across as slow for some). His courses usually have projects and assignments that are easy to ace, but be sure to study for the final! There's no surprises if you STUDY and put in effort :)

This course is no doubt not completely easy, you have to put in the work in order to understand the material, however Dr. Bijan puts in a lot of effort to make this course as straightforward as possible. The final was pretty fair, only issue was 30 MC in 30 minutes, however long answer questions were quite easy. Definitely practice as much as u can

he TRIES to sympathizes with students with the fact that we are all stressed and busy because of COVID. No clear expectations/unclear assignments, concepts on assignments aren't fully taught, assignments are alot of work for only 5% of final grade. There are no extensions either. Final is 50% of the final mark. So much for "sympathizing" with us.
Final exam will ruin your mark and your life
Most difficult exam Ive gotten
Giant workload and overly high expectations from students. Take MIS with any other prof and your life will be much easier.

This prof has been unreasonable all semester (with workload and grades). For our final, we have 30 minutes to answer 32 multiple choice questions and then 2 hours to write two reports, totalling 10 pages. Its tough to explain with the word limit, but he is the worst and most unreasonable prof Ive ever had.
Terrible prof. Does not listen to any student feedback. Makes things unnecessarily difficult and has ridiculous expectations.

Great professor who cares more about teaching than just completing a syllabus. Makes expectations extremely clear and will go as far as giving a long list of exam questions to help you study. One of the best professors at U of Ottawa.

Great prof, really wants to see his students excel. Has four case studies throughout the semester which are basically free grades, and a final presentation which is half graded by him, half by peers (and he grades kinder than the students). Would take this prof again 10/10

Taught Module 3 of the course. Lectures are boring!!! He takes forever to get his point across making the lecture long. The TAs, with exception of 2, are not helpful when it comes to Access. Professor does not seem to be well aligned with the assignment, but he always puts a strong effort to help you. He is very friendly and makes an easy quiz.

Hate Access, not the prof. He teaches the Access module for ADM1370, and unfortunately, Access will make you hate this class. He's a good lecturer and his quizzes are easy. Come to class, you'll already know 20% of the questions on his quiz. Make sure to go to the lab session though!! Otherwise  you'll be suck the night before crying over Access.
Good lecturer. Well prepared. Willing to help. Content is dry but not too difficult.
He is a really nice person. The class itself is boring but it has nothing to do with the prof. He is easy and approachable and you can really talk to him when you have a problem.

Useless prof, terrible slides, barely teaches us anything on access, and expects us to be experts. Schedules lab exercises on the first few days in the course and none until the end. Complete waste of time, would never take another course again. Also quite boring
Very helpful professor. Clear lectures and really listens to students' feedback. Highly recommended!
The content of the course is very boring. He didn't make me want to pay attention. His assignments are easy but a bit confusing. TAs are not very good.

he always deceived us about his research interests. I went to him to get project in production mangement and after several weeks he informed me that he is only interested in MIS. He has corrected his research interests on his web page.

Point-form notes: ->Take him, trust me. ->Boring due to material. ->Very good clear assignments. ->Very organized. ->Midterms have one or two surprises but that's it. ->VERY helpful in office hours. ->EXCELLENT course website (designed by himself) ->If he had a little more confidence (and better ENGLISH) he would be AMAZING!  Beej ;)
Great Teacher, seems interested in what he does.
He is a very good lecturer. Knows his stuff well.
